datasets.name: 39a5402c
queryLines:
WITH TopTopics AS (
    SELECT topic 
    FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean 
    
    GROUP BY topic ORDER BY COUNT(ticket_id) DESC LIMIT 10
    ), 
    
    TopCountries AS (
        SELECT country 
        FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean 
       -- WHERE country not in ('Japan','Australia') -- for map rendering
        --WHERE COUNTRY IN ('United States', 'France', 'Germany', 'Italy', 'Spain', 'United Kingdom', 'Canada', 'Australia', 'Japan','Netherlands')
        GROUP BY country ORDER BY COUNT(ticket_id) DESC --LIMIT 10
    ) 
    
SELECT s.* except(s.ticket_id), a.* except(a.ticket_id), t.*,resolution_time  as adjusted_resolution_time
, dayname(close_time) as day_of_week
, hour(close_time) as hour_of_day 
--, (s.resolution_time + CASE WHEN t.support_level = 'Tier 2' THEN FLOOR(3000 + (RAND() * (3000 - 2400))) ELSE 0 END)  AS adjusted_resolution_time 
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.sla_clean s 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.agents_clean a USING (ticket_id) 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean t USING (ticket_id) 
Where t.country IN (SELECT country FROM TopCountries)

columns.expression: sum(case when agent_group = 'AI-Assisted' then  operational_cost end)*100/sum(operational_cost)

datasets.name: 916033f4
queryLines:
SELECT t.country, COUNT(s.ticket_id) AS support_volume 
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.sla_clean s 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.agents_clean a ON s.ticket_id = a.ticket_id 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean t ON s.ticket_id = t.ticket_id 
GROUP BY t.country;

datasets.name: 44cccafd
queryLines:
SELECT t.topic, COUNT(s.ticket_id) AS support_volume, (COUNT(s.ticket_id) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean)) AS percentage 
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.sla_clean s 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.agents_clean a ON s.ticket_id = a.ticket_id 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean t ON s.ticket_id = t.ticket_id 
GROUP BY t.topic;

datasets.name: 56d2ee72
queryLines:
SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN t.status = 'In progress' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS in_progress_tickets
, SUM(CASE WHEN t.status = 'Closed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS closed_tickets
, SUM(CASE WHEN t.status = 'Resolved' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS resolved_tickets 
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.sla_clean s 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.agents_clean a ON s.ticket_id = a.ticket_id 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean t ON s.ticket_id = t.ticket_id

datasets.name: a3408347
queryLines:
SELECT
  a.agent_group,
  close_time,
  sum(t.operational_cost) over (partition by a.agent_group order by close_time) as cumulative_cost
  
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.sla_clean s 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.agents_clean a USING (ticket_id) 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean t USING (ticket_id)
ORDER BY
  a.agent_group,
  close_time;

datasets.name: 24061a29
queryLines:
WITH original_table AS (
    SELECT 
  DATE_TRUNC("MONTH", `close_time`) AS close_time,
  COUNT(`ticket_id`) AS ticket_id
FROM (
    WITH TopTopics AS (
    SELECT topic 
    FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean 
    GROUP BY topic ORDER BY COUNT(ticket_id) DESC --LIMIT 10
    ), 
    
    TopCountries AS (
        SELECT country 
        FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean 
        GROUP BY country ORDER BY COUNT(ticket_id) DESC LIMIT 5
    ) 
    
SELECT s.*, a.* except(a.ticket_id), t.* except(t.ticket_id),resolution_time  as adjusted_resolution_time
--, (s.resolution_time + CASE WHEN t.support_level = 'Tier 2' THEN FLOOR(3000 + (RAND() * (3000 - 2400))) ELSE 0 END)  AS adjusted_resolution_time 
FROM `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.sla_clean s 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.agents_clean a USING (ticket_id) 
JOIN `axel_richier`.`aibi_customer_support_update`.tickets_clean t USING (ticket_id) 

WHERE t.topic IN (SELECT topic FROM TopTopics) AND t.country IN (SELECT country FROM TopCountries) AND   s.resolution_time != 0
) GROUP BY 1
  ),
  dates AS (
    SELECT 
      MAX(close_time) AS max_date_column,
      MIN(close_time) AS min_date_column,
      MAX_BY(ticket_id, close_time) AS ticket_id
    FROM original_table
  ),
  forecast_table AS (
    SELECT 
      close_time,
      ticket_id_forecast,
      ticket_id_upper,
      ticket_id_lower,
      NULL AS ticket_id
    FROM AI_FORECAST(
      TABLE(original_table),
      horizon => (
        SELECT
          max_date_column + MAKE_DT_INTERVAL(CAST(FLOOR(DATEDIFF(max_date_column, min_date_column) * 0.5) AS INT), 0, 0, 0)
        FROM dates
      ),
      time_col => 'close_time',
      value_col => 'ticket_id'
    )
  )

  SELECT * FROM forecast_table
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    close_time,
    NULL AS ticket_id_forecast,
    NULL AS ticket_id_upper,
    NULL AS ticket_id_lower,
    ticket_id
  FROM original_table
    WHERE close_time < (SELECT max_date_column FROM dates)
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    max_date_column AS close_time,
    ticket_id AS ticket_id_forecast,
    ticket_id AS ticket_id_upper,
    ticket_id AS ticket_id_lower,
    ticket_id
  FROM
    dates

datasets.name: 4fd6c763
queryLines:
SELECT 
    date,
    ROUND(customer_satisfaction * 100, 1) as customer_satisfaction_pct,
    ROUND(query_success_rate * 100, 1) as query_success_rate_pct,
    total_daily_interactions,
    daily_active_users,
    ROUND(avg_response_time_ms, 0) as avg_response_time_ms,
    ROUND(median_tickets_resolved_per_agent, 1) as median_tickets_per_agent,
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN 'Internal Testing'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date < '2025-05-15' THEN 'External Launch (Issues)'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-15' THEN 'Post-Fix (Resolved)'
        ELSE 'Other'
    END as phase
FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.ceo_kpis
WHERE date >= DATE(:start_date) 
    AND date <= DATE(:end_date)
ORDER BY date

datasets.name: 614de99b
queryLines:

    ROUND(avg_tickets_resolved_per_agent, 1) as avg_tickets_per_agent,
    active_agents_count,

FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.agent_productivity_metrics
WHERE date >= DATE(:start_date) 
    AND date <= DATE(:end_date)
ORDER BY date

datasets.name: 803f416d
queryLines:
SELECT 
    :parameter as analysis_date,
    topic,
    total_queries,
    ROUND(failure_rate * 100, 1) as failure_rate_pct,
    ROUND(poor_feedback_rate * 100, 1) as poor_feedback_rate_pct,
    ROUND(avg_response_time_ms, 0) as avg_response_time_ms,
    CASE 
        WHEN topic = 'usage_inquiry' AND :parameter >= '2024-05-01' AND :parameter < '2024-05-15' THEN '🔴 Known Issue'
        WHEN failure_rate >= 0.5 THEN '🚨 Critical'
        WHEN failure_rate >= 0.2 THEN '⚠️  Warning'
        ELSE '✅ Normal'
    END as status
FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.topic_failure_metrics
WHERE date = :parameter
    AND total_queries >= 5  -- Only show topics with meaningful volume
ORDER BY failure_rate DESC, total_queries DESC

datasets.name: b13ac2d8
queryLines:
SELECT 
    date,
    business_phase,
    ai_impact,
    
    -- Key Customer Metrics
    csat_percentage,
    fcr_percentage,
    customer_experience_index,
    
    -- Operational Metrics  
    median_tickets_resolved_per_agent,
    total_daily_interactions,
    query_success_percentage,
    
    -- Performance Indicators
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN '📊 Baseline'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date < '2025-05-15' THEN '🚨 Issues Discovered'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-15' THEN '🚀 Optimized Performance'
    END as status_indicator
    
FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.extended_ceo_kpis
WHERE date >= DATE(:start_date) 
    AND date <= DATE(:end_date)
ORDER BY date

datasets.name: dafe925f
queryLines:
SELECT 
    date,
    business_phase,
    phase_indicator,
    
    -- The three lines for your dashboard
    overall_csat_percentage,
    positive_feedback_csat_percentage,
    negative_feedback_csat_percentage,
    
    -- Additional metrics
    csat_spread_percentage,
    
    -- Period context
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN 'Pre-Launch Baseline'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date < '2025-05-15' THEN 'Issue Discovery Period'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-15' THEN 'Post-Fix Recovery'
    END as period_description
    
FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.three_line_csat_trends
WHERE date >= DATE(:start_date) 
    AND date <= DATE(:end_date)
ORDER BY date

datasets.name: 5189cb1d
queryLines:
SELECT 
    date,
    business_phase,
    
    -- Phase indicator for visual cues
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN '📊 Baseline'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date <= '2025-05-15' THEN '🚀 AI Launch'
        WHEN date > '2025-05-15' THEN '📈 AI Optimized'
    END as phase_indicator,
    
    -- The two main lines for your CSAT dashboard
    without_ai_agent as csat_without_ai_percentage,
    with_ai_agent as csat_with_ai_percentage,
    
    -- Additional metrics for analysis
    improvement_percentage as csat_improvement_points,
    
    -- AI adoption progress (for secondary analysis)
    days_since_ai_launch,
    
    -- Period context descriptions
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN 'Pre-AI Baseline Period'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date < '2025-05-15' THEN 'AI Launch & Early Adoption'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-15' AND date < '2025-06-01' THEN 'AI Optimization Phase'
        WHEN date >= '2025-06-01' THEN 'Mature AI Performance'
    END as period_description,
    
    -- Performance status indicator
    CASE 
        WHEN with_ai_agent IS NULL THEN 'Baseline Only'
        WHEN improvement_percentage >= 5.0 THEN '🟢 Strong AI Impact'
        WHEN improvement_percentage >= 2.0 THEN '🟡 Moderate AI Impact'
        WHEN improvement_percentage >= 0.0 THEN '🟠 Slight AI Impact'
        ELSE '🔴 Below Baseline'
    END as performance_status
    
FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.ai_agent_performance_demo
WHERE metric_type = 'CSAT'
    AND date >= DATE(:start_date) 
    AND date <= DATE(:end_date)
ORDER BY date;

datasets.name: bfc6f9fa
queryLines:
SELECT 
    date,
    business_phase,
    
    -- Phase indicator for visual cues
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN '📊 Baseline'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date <= '2025-05-15' THEN '🚀 AI Launch'
        WHEN date > '2025-05-15' THEN '📈 AI Optimized'
    END as phase_indicator,
    
    -- The two main lines for your FCR dashboard
    without_ai_agent as fcr_without_ai_percentage,
    with_ai_agent as fcr_with_ai_percentage,
    
    -- Additional metrics for analysis
    improvement_percentage as fcr_improvement_points,
    
    -- Efficiency context (FCR directly impacts operational costs)
    CASE 
        WHEN without_ai_agent >= 75.0 THEN 'High Baseline Efficiency'
        WHEN without_ai_agent >= 65.0 THEN 'Standard Baseline Efficiency'  
        ELSE 'Low Baseline Efficiency'
    END as baseline_efficiency_tier,
    
    -- AI adoption progress
    days_since_ai_launch,
    
    -- Period context descriptions
    CASE 
        WHEN date < '2025-05-01' THEN 'Pre-AI Baseline Period'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-01' AND date < '2025-05-15' THEN 'AI Launch & Integration'
        WHEN date >= '2025-05-15' AND date < '2025-06-01' THEN 'AI Learning & Optimization'
        WHEN date >= '2025-06-01' THEN 'Mature AI-Assisted Operations'
    END as period_description,
    
    -- Operational impact indicator
    CASE 
        WHEN with_ai_agent IS NULL THEN 'Baseline Operations'
        WHEN with_ai_agent >= 80.0 THEN '🟢 Excellent FCR Performance'
        WHEN with_ai_agent >= 75.0 THEN '🟡 Good FCR Performance'
        WHEN with_ai_agent >= 70.0 THEN '🟠 Average FCR Performance'
        ELSE '🔴 Below Target FCR'
    END as operational_status,
    
    -- Cost impact estimation (higher FCR = lower operational costs)
    CASE 
        WHEN improvement_percentage >= 8.0 THEN 'Significant Cost Savings'
        WHEN improvement_percentage >= 5.0 THEN 'Moderate Cost Savings'
        WHEN improvement_percentage >= 2.0 THEN 'Minor Cost Savings'
        WHEN improvement_percentage > 0.0 THEN 'Marginal Cost Savings'
        ELSE 'No Cost Impact'
    END as cost_impact_category
    
FROM telco_customer_support_dev.agent_kpis.ai_agent_performance_demo
WHERE metric_type = 'First Contact Resolution'
    AND date >= DATE(:start_date) 
    AND date <= DATE(:end_date)
ORDER BY date;
